:: Nightmare Witch
<<effects>><<nightmareStart "witch">><<set $location to "old_temple">>
<<set Time.setTime(18, 30)>><<set Weather.set("heavyClouds", true)>>

You fall into a restless sleep. You toss and turn. It feels as though you're sleeping on cold stone.
<br><br>

You jolt up to the sound of a whip cracking, and someone crying out in pain.
<br><br>

You rub your eyes, struggling to see through the gloom. A torch casts the long shadow of a whip over you, as it comes down again.
<br><br>

You see a man with long blond hair in a suit of chainmail, with a large black cloth adorned over it.
His back is turned to you. He brings his whip down one last time, before stepping aside and fading away into the stone wall.
<br><br>

<<if $nightmaresSeen.includes("witch")>>
	You know this place. It isn't real, you don't think. The witch slowly looks up at you as she pants for breath. <span class="pink">She seems to faintly recognise you.</span>
	<br><br>

	<<link [[Wake up|Nightmare Witch Wake]]>><</link>><<nightmareWakeDifficulty>>
	<br>
	<<link [[Talk|Nightmare Witch 2]]>><</link>>
	<br>
<<else>>
	A woman sits, bound by silver manacles, against the wall. She slowly looks up at you as she pants for breath.
	<br><br>

	Her grey eye widens in surprise upon seeing you. She coughs. <span class="pink">Glowing pink fluid trails down her chin into a silver vessel.</span>
	<br><br>

	You can't help but feel she looks familiar. The left half of her face is obscured by swirling shadows, while the right sports a fresh burn.
	<br><br>

	<<link [[다음|Nightmare Witch 2]]>><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>

:: Nightmare Witch Wake
<<effects>>

You know the way out. You unlock the cell door and leave the dungeon, looking over your shoulder one last time.
<br><br>

<<if $willpowerSuccess>>
	You resist the urge to turn around. She isn't real.
	<br><br>

	<<link [[다음|Nightmare Witch End]]>><</link>>
	<br>
<<else>>
	You walk down the corridor, up the long stone steps, and emerge... back in her cell. She stares at you.
	<br><br>

	You sit down.
	<br><br>

	<<link [[다음|Nightmare Witch 2]]>><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>

:: Nightmare Witch 2
<<effects>>

She dissolves into blackness as the torch goes out.
<br><br>

Another torch is lit in the cell. She appears under it, now naked, being scrubbed down and washed by the same man from before.
<br><br>

A black antler emerges from the left side of her head. The man disappears again. She starts to crawl towards you, her mouth hanging open, revealing no tongue within.
<br><br>

She says nothing, but you can hear words being spoken into your head.
<br><br>

<<if $nightmaresSeen.includes("witch")>>
	'Why did you return?'
<<else>>
	'Did you enjoy watching me suffer?'
<</if>>
<br><br>

She doesn't wait for your answer. Her shadow turns, passing over the torch, snuffing it out.
<br><br>

<<link [[다음|Nightmare Witch 3]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Witch 3
<<effects>>

Another torch flickers to life. She and the gaoler appear again. A cross is being branded into her flesh.
<br><br>

She's screaming in pain, but the words continue. 'This isn't your prison.'
<br><br>

A torrent of silver needles fall from the ceiling. She vanishes behind them.
The needles all land in a bucket.
<br><br>

Another torch is lit. The two are sharing a stolen meal.
<br><br>

The words become more clear. 'I am trapped in this story. Reliving it over and over. It has been... so long.
I know not which retelling is accurate. Each has pieces of the truth lost in lies. I have heard... seen it so many times. Who am I?'
<br><br>

<<link [[Tell the witch her name|Nightmare Witch 4]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Say nothing|Nightmare Witch 4]]>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Witch 4
<<effects>>

<<if $phase is 1>>
	You try to say her name aloud. The word refuses to leave your lips. Yet, she seemed to hear it.
	<br><br>

	'That is what the townsfolk called me. Was it my true name?' She shakes her head, uncertain.
<<else>>
	You sit in silence.
	<br><br>

	'Perhaps the name should remain lost.' She shakes her head, uncertain.
<</if>>
'I do not... I do not go by that name any longer. That name passed on with...'
<br><br>

Her expression becomes unreadable as the gaoler reappears in front of her, gently covering her with a bedsheet.
<br><br>

'...him.' She stares.
<br><br>

'I believe... we are both dreaming. You, and whomever I am a memory of. I keep returning here. Others who hear the tale end up here, sometimes. The story is a curse.
Am I truly her? I awaken, and forget, until I am brought here again. And again. And again. And again. And again.'
<br><br>

<span class="red">A coil of chains slithers around you like a snake.</span> The room flips, and you're suddenly hanging from the ceiling.
She looks at you apologetically. 'Just remain still. This is not your prison. You will not face punishment, for you have not transgressed.'
<br><br>

You swing back and forth, making your stomach rise.
<<if $nightmaresSeen.includes("witch")>>
	'Has your answer changed since last we met? Grant me closure that I might find rest.'
<<else>>
	'You... you may be able to aid me. Provide me relief, however temporary.'
<</if>>
<br><br>

She reappears with the gaoler. They are embracing.
'Which do you <span class="gold">believe</span> rings the most true?'
<br><br>

<<if $hcEndings.includes("S")>>
	<<link [[Faith|Nightmare Witch Faith]]>><</link>>
<<else>>
	<span class="black">You haven't heard this version of the story yet.</span>
<</if>>
<br>
<<if $hcEndings.includes("A")>>
	<<link [[Love|Nightmare Witch Love]]>><</link>>
<<else>>
	<span class="black">You haven't heard this version of the story yet.</span>
<</if>>
<br>
<<if $hcEndings.includes("B")>>
	<<link [[Desperation|Nightmare Witch Desperation]]>><</link>>
<<else>>
	<span class="black">You haven't heard this version of the story yet.</span>
<</if>>
<br>
<<if $hcEndings.includes("C")>>
	<<link [[Perdition|Nightmare Witch Perdition]]>><</link>>
<<else>>
	<span class="black">You haven't heard this version of the story yet.</span>
<</if>>
<br>
<<if $hcEndings.includes("D")>>
	<<link [[Stagnation|Nightmare Witch Stagnation]]>><</link>>
<<else>>
	<span class="black">You haven't heard this version of the story yet.</span>
<</if>>
<br>
<<if $hcEndings.includes("E")>>
	<<link [[Paranoia|Nightmare Witch Paranoia]]>><</link>>
<<else>>
	<span class="black">You haven't heard this version of the story yet.</span>
<</if>>
<br>
<<if $hcEndings.includes("F")>>
	<<link [[Hatred|Nightmare Witch Hatred]]>><</link>>
<<else>>
	<span class="black">You haven't heard this version of the story yet.</span>
<</if>>
<br>
<<link [[Say nothing|Nightmare Witch Nothing]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Witch Faith
<<effects>><<set Weather.set("lightPrecipitation", true)>><<set $location to "forest">>

She lets out a soft laugh as recognition crosses her face. She fades away. 'If only it could be the whole truth.
I was still his prisoner. My love for him did not change that simple fact. I could not walk. I was weak.'
<br><br>

She reappears in the gaoler's arms. He's carrying her away into the forest. Her fists clench, and her face falls to an expression of terrible understanding.
'I would gladly accept being his prisoner alone. Yet, I did not expect to remain his prisoner after my body had died.'
She suddenly looks afraid. The tears begin to flow. 'Why must you believe this one? This...'
<br><br>

The scene fades away, before coming back into focus. You're in a small wooden cabin. She sits in a rocking chair. The gaoler kneels before her, his head pressed into her... baby bump.
She wipes her eyes. 'This is why I can never forget. This is why I remain trapped here. He made me so happy. So very happy. A heretic, a monster like me did not deserve it.'
<br><br>

The scene fades away again. You're outside, the sound of gentle rain and wind meeting your ears.
<br><br>

The gaoler sits on the grass in front of a stone object. Beside him, a little girl in a green dress stands sobbing. The chains are gone. You approach.
<br><br>

You peer over the gaoler's shoulder. It's a grave marker. A stone cross, engraved with a name.
<br><br>

<span class="narration">Nona ap Fayne</span>
<br><br>

The girl turns to you, as if suddenly able to see you.
<br><br>

"Thank you," she says with Nona's voice. "I'll forget when I come here again. But thank you, even for just one night's rest..."
<br><br>

<<link [[Wake up|Nightmare Witch End]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Witch Love
<<effects>><<set Weather.set("clear", true)>><<set $location to "forest">>
<<set Time.setTime(23, 0)>>

She fades away, laughing with devious glee.
<br><br>

The gaoler appears, strings attached to his head and limbs. The demon towers above you, working his strings like a puppet.
<br><br>

"He was so eager to give me his heart. Was it so wrong for me to take it?" Her voice sounds more real, yet there's an eerie hiss to it. A tentacle in her mouth acts as her tongue. She puts a hand up to it and giggles as they both vanish again.
<br><br>

A stone altar appears before you. They both lie on it, and she moans in ecstasy. A regal pair of antlers adorn her head, a pair of purple wings on her back.
"He was h... hhhaaappy. I know that much to be true, from- ah! From this telling."
<br><br>

Her legs, enwreathed in tentacles, wrap around his waist as he reaches climax. "It would have been a waste to let him be free. He was mine. Mine alone."
<br><br>

They vanish once more. She appears behind you, walking on legs braced by tentacles. Her blackened, elongated arms nearly touch the ground. The gaoler stumbles behind her.
Her look of smug superiority fades into a sad smile. "In truth, I think he and I were both prisoners. Prisoners and gaolers of one another. As cold as my heart was..."
<br><br>

A tear rolls down the demon's cheek. "I did not want to let him go. I could not. Perhaps I did not love him, but I know he loved me. It was something I could indulge, if nothing else."
<br><br>

She puts a black claw over her chest, and the other over her tummy. "No... no, there was more. I—wait, don't leave! We were so close to the truth!"
<br><br>

<<link [[Wake up|Nightmare Witch End]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Witch Desperation
<<effects>><<set Weather.set("clear", true)>><<set $location to "forest">>
<<set Time.setTime(23, 0)>>

She fades away, and something roars in the distance.
<br><br>

'There's... familiarity here. Many truths, and many lies. It falters in context.' Four long, glassy, spider-like limbs reach out from the dark, carrying her broken body.
<br><br>

'Was this the end? No. I remember. This is the story that ends best for him.' An approximation of a sad smile crosses her split jaws.
'He was looking for me. I was looking for him, too. I believed myself to be the monster that the cloister made me. Despite that, I wished to see him one last time before my body failed.'
<br><br>

She fades away. You're in a small clearing. The gaoler is holding an infant with tiny twig-like antlers on her head.
<br><br>

'We did see each other again, although he would never realise it.' The bushes rustle as someone flees the clearing.
<br><br>

A person with leaves in their hair turns to you. You don't catch what they say before you wake up.
<br><br>

<<link [[Wake up|Nightmare Witch End]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Witch Perdition
<<effects>>

She vanishes, and reappears with a silk cord around her neck. Her face is flushed and full of sadistic desire.
<br><br>

She brings down a black claw on a man in monk's robes. The gaoler stands behind her, whipping the monk if he moves too much.
<br><br>

She seems embarrassed. 'I remember. I was terrified of the hounds after what they did to me.
This... act of ours, it helped alleviate my mental strain. It was only ever us, though. I was never used to punish the sins of others.'
<br><br>

She obediently barks at her master. The gaoler lifts her, carrying her like a princess to their bedchamber.
<br><br>

'Did I grow affectionate for him? I must have. There was so much more than this, however. This was only a fraction of a truth.'
<br><br>

<<link [[Wake up|Nightmare Witch End]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Witch Stagnation
<<effects>>

Her body slumps over, like an unwanted doll cast aside.
<br><br>

'Trapped. Trapped within a broken body, unable to move, forever.' Her skin takes on the texture of fabric. She's suddenly impaled by countless silver needles. Cotton spills from her insides.
<br><br>

'It was maddening. He... helped me. His pure touch granted me strength. Clarity.' One by one, the needles are pulled out. A pair of hands gently pick her up.
<br><br>

The gaoler holds the doll up to his cheek, before vanishing.
<br><br>

He reappears with a sewing needle, stitching closed the countless <span class="tentacle">holes</span> in the doll. His fingers are covered in small bandages.
<br><br>

When he's finished, he turns around and hands the doll to someone. A little girl, who looks a lot like the witch, and a lot like him too.
She looks up to him with wonder, before hugging his waist. He returns the embrace.
<br><br>

She runs off into another room, where the witch sits in a rocking chair. The girl shows her the doll with pure joy, jumping up and down. The witch smiles warmly.
<br><br>

Her face suddenly changes to confusion. 'I... I don't understand...'
<br><br>

<<link [[Wake up|Nightmare Witch End]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Witch Paranoia
<<effects>>

She vanishes, along with the cell. Empty red light surrounds you.
<br><br>

'The cloister. They called themselves family, yet they so often turned their wrath on one another.'
<br><br>

The gaoler appears, wearing rags, bound to a chunk of wall floating in the nothingness.
<br><br>

'It did not end like this. There was doubt in his heart, this much is true. It drove him to do... something.
I can't remember what.'
<br><br>

His chains suddenly burst, falling far below. He begins to run towards a stone altar.
<br><br>

'No closure, only more questions.'
<br><br>

<<link [[Wake up|Nightmare Witch End]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Witch Hatred
<<effects>>

Her limp legs begin to fuse together. Her body elongates.
<br><br>

The serpent coils around you. Her face comes very close to yours. <span class="red">Your joints all lock up, and you can't move!</span>
<br><br>

'There was much hatred between us. This is true. It would eventually destroy us.' She tightens around you. <span class="red">You can't breathe.</span> 'Suffocating, binding hatred.'
<br><br>

You shed your skin. She emerges from you.
<br><br>

<<link [[Wake up|Nightmare Witch End]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Witch Nothing
<<effects>>

She vanishes.
<br><br>

'Is the only way to be free to forget?'
<br><br>

A long silence follows.
<br><br>

'If I forget this, I may forget everything.'
<br><br>

<<link [[Wake up|Nightmare Witch End]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Witch End
<<effects>><<nightmareEnd>>

You shiver as you wake.
<br><br>

It was only a dream. A story is just a story.
<br><br>

<<link [[다음|$nightmareExit]]>><<unset $nightmareExit>><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Gwylan
<<effects>><<nightmareStart "gwylan">><<set $location to "docks">>
<<set Time.setTime(15, 33)>><<set Weather.set("heavyClouds", true)>>
<<npc Gwylan>><<person1>><<set $dockCount to 2>>
You smell salt in the air, and open your eyes. You're at the docks on Mer Street.
<br><br>

A <<personsimple>> stands at the very end of the furthest dock, <<his>> mousy hair blowing in the wind. <<He>> gently sways to a rhythm you can't hear, <span class="teal">but know</span>.
<br><br>

<<if $nightmaresSeen.includes("gwylan")>>
	You know what this is. The ocean threatens to swallow you already. It isn't real, you hope.
	<br><br>

	<<link [[Wake up|Nightmare Gwylan Wake]]>><</link>><<gwylanWillpowerDifficulty>>
	<br>
<<else>>
	You squint, trying to see clearly. Your eyes sting. The reflection on the top of the ocean is nearly perfect in clarity. For a moment, you feel like you're falling upwards.
	<br><br>
<</if>>
<<link [[Approach|Nightmare Gwylan 2]]>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Leave|Nightmare Gwylan Leave]]>><</link>>
