:: Nightmare Gwylan 3
<<effects>>
<<if $phase is "talk">>
	You open your mouth to speak, but only whalesong escapes.
<<elseif $phase is "leave">>
	You turn to leave, but your legs aren't there anymore.
<<else>>
	You reach out to <<him>>, but the space between you is infinite. <<He>> can touch you, yet you can't touch <<him>>.
<</if>>
<br><br>
<<set $phase to 0>>

You hear a low gurgle.
<br><br>

The ocean's surface reflects silver manacles and needles.
<br><br>

It reflects planes flying overhead, dropping payloads that float upward. They fall forever.
<br><br>

It reflects a neverending array of burning docks in the sky, spinning into each other in endless ruin.
<br><br>

It reflects the forest.
<br><br>

A circle forms in the water before <<him>>.
<br><br>

It reflects everything.
<br><br>

Water droplets rise, falling into the sky.
<br><br>

It reflects everybody.
<br><br>

The reflection becomes imperfect as the disturbance deepens, a crown of water rising as the clouds darken.
