<br>

:: Nightmare Gwylan 4
<<effects>><<set Weather.set("lightPrecipitation", true)>>
<<if $phase is "look">>
	Your eyes <span class="witch">yearn</span> for the sting of the saltwater.
	<br><br>

	<<He>> turns.
	<br><br>

	<<His>> eye sockets are empty.
	<br><br>

	Yet, you can read <<his>> expression. You can read it painfully well. Ennui. Hopelessness. A tired smile. Saltwater leaks from the corners.
	<br><br>

	<<His>> chest is hollow. <<His>> ribs make a cage for a black, unbeating heart in a void of static.
<<else>>
	You close your eyes, unable to bear the sting of the saltwater anymore.
	<br><br>

	<<He>> turns. You don't know how long <<he>> stares at you, but you can feel <<his>> gaze peeling you apart.
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<His>> mouth opens.
<br><br>

<b>"<span class="witch">All returns to the tide.</span>"</b>
<br><br>

<<link [[...|Nightmare Gwylan Tornado]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Gwylan Tornado
<<effects>><<set Weather.set("heavyPrecipitation", true)>>
The circle of water rises into the sky to meet the clouds. It spins in a vortex, screaming as though it were in pain. It grows.
<br><br>

The wind rushes towards it. You feel yourself being pulled in. It grows further.
<br><br>

The entire horizon is consumed by the water spout, or perhaps you're already inside of it. The ocean sings in agony.
<br><br>

Gwylan takes your hands with a loving smile. You feel it gnaw at your spine.
<<if $phase is "close">>
	When did your eyes open? Why are Gwylan's eyes empty?
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<link [[Return|Nightmare Gwylan Whalefall]]>><<set $phase to "go">><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Resist|Nightmare Gwylan Whalefall]]>><<set $phase to "stay">><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Gwylan Whalefall
<<effects>>

<<He>> says something to you, but you can't hear it over the death scream of the sea.
<br><br>

<<He>> pulls on your hands, and starts to fall backwards.
<<if $phase is "go">>
	You step forward in turn, taking the plunge with <<him>>.
	<br><br>

	You embrace as you break the surface.
	<br><br>

	<<He>> sighs with relief. Or maybe that was you. Neither of you will be alone in the end, at least.
	<br><br>

	You pull your head back to look at <<him>> one last time, before the last light of the surface winks out.
	<<His>> eyes are no longer empty. <<His>> tears float upwards past you. <<He>> smiles lovingly, and <<his>> heart starts to beat.
	<br><br>

	The screams of the world fade away as you sink yet further. You're plunged into the darkness of the ocean floor.
	<br><br>

	With one final embrace, the two of you land at the bottom, at long last.
	<br><br>

	You settle into the sediment, kicking up silt. <<His>> hands dig into your back and you hold <<him>> tighter, each of you making sure the other is still there in the pitch-blackness. Your heartbeats ring out together.
	<br><br>

	Your bodies nourish the rebirth of the world. Your ribcages link in an eternal embrace. Nobody remembers either of you.
<<else>>
	You refuse to leave. <<He>> falls regardless, <span class="red">taking your hands with <<him>></span>.
	<br><br>

	<<His>> smile vanishes, replaced by a look of agonising betrayal. A thin black line shoots down from the sky, straight through <<his>> heart. You've broken a promise.
	<br><br>

	<<He>> vanishes under the waves.
	<br><br>

	You stand alone in the vortex. You remain in a vast sea of nothing, an abyss that will never support life again. You never remember who was here with you. The sky goes dark.
<</if>>
<<set $phase to 0>>
<br><br>

<<link [[다음|Nightmare Gwylan End]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Nightmare Gwylan End
<<effects>><<nightmareEnd>>

You shiver and cough as you wake. Your tongue is horribly dry, and you feel like there's a hole in your chest.
<br><br>

It was only a dream. You feel dizzy.
<br><br>

<<link [[다음|$nightmareExit]]>><<unset $nightmareExit>><</link>>
